    11	## §1. Stage Matrix
    12	
    13	Every stage has exactly one **Performer** and one **Cross-Validator**. Self-approval forbidden.
    14	
    15	| # | Stage | Performer | Cross-Validator | Pattern | Artifact |
    16	|---|-------|-----------|----------------|---------|----------|
    17	| 1 | Overall Planning | Claude Code + Codex (co-propose) | Human | Serial (propose → approve) | `meetings/<round>_plan.md` |
    18	| 2 | Detailed Design | Codex | Claude Code | Serial | `contracts/<round>/spec.md` |
    19	| 3 | Convention / Linter Lock | Claude Code | Codex | Serial | `contracts/<round>/convention_version.txt`, `lint_config.txt` |
    20	| 4 | Eval Protocol Authoring | Codex | Claude Code | Serial | `contracts/<round>/eval_protocol.md` |
    21	| 5 | Acceptance Criteria | Codex | Claude Code | Serial | `contracts/<round>/acceptance.md` |
    22	| 6 | Round Lock Creation | Claude Code (runs checker) | Codex (reviews lock JSON) | Serial | `locks/<round>.lock` |
    23	| 7 | Coding 1st Pass | Claude Code | Codex (architecture + code review) | Parallel only with disjoint whitelists/worktrees | Commit(s) + `meetings/<round>_review1.md` |
    24	| 8 | Runtime Evidence Capture | Claude Code (following §4 eval protocol) | Codex (reviews report completeness) | Parallel across screens/scenarios | `reports/<round>/evidence/*` |
    25	| 9 | Evaluation Verdict | Codex | Claude Code (checks verdict is grounded in evidence) | Serial | `reports/<round>/verdict.md` |
    26	| 10 | Gate 2 Three-Evaluator | red_team_reviewer, hig_guardian, visual_qa (parallel fork) | Cross-agreement rule (Gate 3) | **Parallel** | `reports/<round>/gate2/*` |
    27	| 11 | Coding 2nd Pass (remediation) | Codex + Claude Code (co-decide) → Claude Code (implements) | Codex (re-reviews) | Serial | Commit(s) + `meetings/<round>_review2.md` |
    28	| 12 | Round Retro | Claude Code + Codex | Human | Serial | `round_retro/<round>.md` |
    29	| 13 | Regulation Update (if any) | Proposer operator | Other operator | Serial | Amendment meeting + CHANGELOG |
    30	
    31	### Stage precedence within a round
    32	
    33	Stages 1–6 must complete before stage 7 begins. Stage 7–11 may interleave with amendment meetings. Stage 12 only after all Gate 1–5 pass. Stage 13 is optional and triggered only if retro identifies regulation debt.
    34	
    35	## §2. Parallel vs Serial Rules
    36	
    37	**Parallel permitted when:**
    38	- Independent evidence gathering across disjoint screens/scenarios (stage 8)
    39	- Gate 2 three-evaluator fork (stage 10) — dedicated role contracts, no shared state
    40	- Implementation across disjoint `file_whitelist` partitions AND separate worktrees
    41	
    42	**Serial required when:**
    43	- Contract-setting (stages 2–6): sequential review preserves authorship attribution
    44	- Approval/merge decisions: single authoritative decision trail
    45	- Amendment meetings: one amendment committed before the next begins
    46	
    47	**Forbidden parallel:**
    48	- Two operators editing the same file concurrently (use meeting + whitelist partition)
    49	- Performer and cross-validator swapping mid-stage (breaks author/verifier separation)
    50	- Parallel evaluation without a locked rubric (stage 8 must follow locked eval_protocol)
    51	
    52	## §3. Ownership Zones
    53	
    54	Default ownership determines who drafts without a meeting. Crossing zones requires a meeting + whitelist expansion.
    55	
    56	### Codex Operator — default owner
    57	
    58	- `operator/contracts/<round>/spec.md` and amendments
    59	- `operator/contracts/<round>/acceptance.md`
