    91	- Any file explicitly marked "USER ONLY" in its header
    92	- Release/tag operations
    93	
    94	## §4. Zone Crossing Protocol
    95	
    96	When a task requires editing a file outside your default zone:
    97	
    98	1. Open a meeting with subject "Zone crossing: <file>"
    99	2. Record reason, scope of edit, reversibility
   100	3. Peer reviews — approves, proposes alternative, or declines
   101	4. On approval: expand `file_whitelist.txt` via amendment (§REGULATION §3)
   102	5. Perform edit → peer reviews output → close meeting
   103	
   104	Shortcut not permitted: you cannot edit first and open meeting after. Caught by Gate 5 drift audit (lock hash mismatch).
   105	
   106	## §5. Evidence ≠ Verdict Rule
   107	
   108	Specific to stage 8 → stage 9 boundary.
   109	
   110	**Claude Code (evidence capture):**
   111	- Follows locked `eval_protocol.md` verbatim
   112	- Produces: raw observations, command output, screenshot paths, simulator/device metadata, timestamps, app state notes
   113	- Forbidden language in capture report: "PASS", "BLOCKER", "ADVISORY", "good", "bad", "acceptable", "regression"
   114	- Permitted language: "screenshot X shows Y", "command Z returned exit W", "element A was/wasn't present"
   115	- Protocol gaps found during capture → stop, open amendment meeting OR mark "capture exception" section with the gap for Codex to address in verdict
   116	
   117	**Codex (verdict authoring):**
   118	- Reads evidence report + locked rubric
   119	- Writes interpretation: PASS/BLOCKER/ADVISORY with specific evidence citations
   120	- May request additional capture if evidence is insufficient (goes back to stage 8 with an amendment)
